Well hey guys, I've just finished my super special secret project. Presenting Link from the Legend of Zelda for NES....<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #00BFFF">IN 3D!</span></strong><br /><br /><br /><img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5023/5812751263_d155b66a0b_z.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Inspired by the totally awesome 3D Dot Game Heroes for the PS3, here's Link from the classic LoZ game from 25 years ago. He's held together with glue and is somewhat fragile, but I'm pretty happy with the overall results. I decided to take the picture out in the forest behind my house - an area perfect for Link! <br /><br />Additional images I took for you guys:<br /><br /><img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5317/5813328976_3b8b98514f_z.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br /><img src="http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5033/5812762959_59784f6c2a_z.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br /><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2028/5812764457_0b356ac41e_z.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br /><img src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2444/5812767453_34c80a0a22_z.jpg" alt="Image" /><br /><br />This project was a lot of fun, but a lot of work even though Link is small at around 4" tall, he contains hundreds of carefully arranged beads and took almost a week to complete. I may visit the idea again sometime, maybe with Mario Megaman and others. <br /><br />Anyway hope you guys like it!<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4236">SatoshiMatrix</a> — Thu Jun 09, 2011 11:44 am</p><hr />
